[## LECTURE 5.2 — DEPENDENCY SCANNING: PIP-AUDIT AND SAFETY]

24
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:30,000
Container scanning finds vulnerabilities in OS packages.
But what about your Python dependencies?
FastAPI, Pydantic, SQLAlchemy, LangChain.

25
00:00:30,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Each one could have vulnerabilities.
You need to scan your pyproject.toml and requirements.txt directly.
Let me show you pip-audit.

26
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:30,000
pip-audit is a tool from the Python Packaging Authority.
It scans dependencies for known vulnerabilities.
Add a dependency-scan job to your CI workflow.

27
00:01:30,000 --> 00:02:00,000
First, setup Python with the correct version.
Install pip-audit and safety.
Then install your package in editable mode with dev dependencies.

28
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:30,000
Run pip-audit with your pyproject.toml as the requirement.
Output SARIF format and include descriptions.
Also run safety check on requirements.txt.

29
00:02:30,000 --> 00:03:00,000
Upload the pip-audit SARIF to GitHub.
Then check if any CRITICAL vulnerabilities were found.
If yes, fail the build.

30
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:30,000
Now automate dependency updates with Dependabot.
Create a dot github forward slash dependabot dot yml file.
For Python dependencies, set the package ecosystem to pip.

31
00:03:30,000 --> 00:04:00,000
Schedule weekly on Monday at 9 AM.
Set open pull requests limit to ten.
Labels include dependencies and security.

32
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:30,000
Group minor and patch updates together to reduce noise.
Only auto-merge security updates.
For Docker base images, also schedule weekly.

33
00:04:30,000 --> 00:05:00,000
Ignore major Python version upgrades.
Stay on your current major version for stability.
For GitHub Actions, also schedule weekly.

34
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:30,000
Now add a pre-commit hook to catch vulnerabilities
before they are even committed.
Create a dot pre-commit-config dot yaml file.

35
00:05:30,000 --> 00:06:00,000
Add the python-safety-dependencies-check hook.
It scans pyproject.toml for vulnerable dependencies.
Add a local pip-audit hook.

36
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:30,000
Now developers get immediate feedback.
If they add an outdated vulnerable package like requests 2.28.0,
the commit is blocked.

37
00:06:30,000 --> 00:07:00,000
The output shows the vulnerability ID, package, severity,
and the title. It also tells them which version to upgrade to.

38
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:30,000
Your lab exercise is to run pip-audit on your pyproject.toml.
Identify any vulnerable dependencies.
Update them to patched versions.

39
00:07:30,000 --> 00:08:00,000
Configure Dependabot for automated updates.
Test the pre-commit hook by intentionally adding
an outdated vulnerable package.

40
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:30,000
In the next lecture, we will detect secrets in Git history.
With Gitleaks and TruffleHog.

